<br>
I surely hope you are correct .. but .. I do not think this will be better for the (volunteer) guides .. who, presumably, will still be assigned to a single server. When there is no GM present on their server, their lives are not easy right now. <br>
<br>
And, unless a major change is made in how a guide can go look for help from the new CS SWAT team, even service for things that guides can do (not much) is likely to be slower than before. I truly feel for the guides out there, who work their tails off, mostly just to receive rudeness from players in return. <br>
<br>
One thing that might be good would be if, as was the subject of this thread originally, all petitions were given a 'number' and that number was known to the petitioner, but I doubt that will happen. On the other hand .. petitions do not survive more than a maximum of 3 hours anyway - or can be deleted much sooner if the petitioner cannot be contacted .. so it might be disheartening to say the least if you got number 65, even if you intended to stay on that long. <br>
<br>
I am beginning to feel as though I will soon be entering a world where, if I left my (real world) credit card at home, I will not survive long. LOL I can see it now ... each time you want to cross into another zone, you will need to pay a toll (kaching, kaching) .. each time you die, the fee for assistance could be in real world dollars .. each time you send a petition, behind the scenes, a bill is being prepared and entered for payment on your account. Well .. perhaps I exaggerate .. but .. I must admit I am beginning to feel as though the American free enterprise system is taking much greater hold in Norrath .. and I am not sure I like it (and not just because of the money aspect). <br>
<br>
Oh well .. we will see. Could be much ado about nothing. But .. I do feel for the guides. Sometimes (on good GM servers), guides loved to go to work .. because there was good comradery and a chance that he/she might run a quest - which, I have heard, is much more fun than just typing to rude petitioners all night. I do think that might change .. and when it does .. the CS will go down, even if the new centralized approach is good. <br>
<br>
<br>
